    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Luis Robert Jr.** anchoring the offensive effort as our highest-rated start (75.16). Facing Ed Rodriguez, **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits from a significant platoon advantage (+14%) and the safety of the #3 spot in the order, making him an elite play despite a slight park penalty. **Jacob Wilson** (64.54) also projects as a strong start; his leadoff assignment provides a high floor for Runs, and he matches up favorably against Weathers, whose 4.06 xERA suggests a prime opportunity for **Jacob Wilson** to capitalize on high-volume plate appearances.\n\nWhile **Jackson Merrill** (60.44) and **Miguel Vargas** (60.08) both cleared our 60-point threshold for strong starts, both are pending official lineup confirmation. **Miguel Vargas** remains a particularly intriguing play if he secures the #3 spot; he benefits from a 13% boost against the pitching profile of Seth Lugo and an additional 5% lift from favorable wind conditions. Conversely, **Liam Hicks** was the most difficult exclusion from the active roster. His 39.83 score fell just shy of the 40-point \"Zebras Floor,\" primarily due to a tough matchup against Lowder (3.31 xERA). Despite the 11% platoon bump, the volatility of facing an elite arm and the potential for a lower-output performance led us to prioritize the stability of our active four-man core over the upside of **Liam Hicks**. \n\nWith core sluggers like **Kyle Tucker**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** sidelined due to scheduling, our focus remains on maximizing efficiency from these targeted matchups. Managers should monitor the official lineup cards for **Miguel Vargas** and **Jackson Merrill** closely; should either slip out of their assumed high-order spots, their efficiency scores will regress accordingly. We continue to prioritize these high-probability opportunities, keeping our deeper bench\u2014including **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Josh Lowe**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Nolan Schanuel**\u2014fresh for upcoming series.",
